  <subsection xml:id="sec-assessments">
    <title>Assessments</title>

    <paragraphs>
      <title>Homework</title>

      <p>
        There will be homework assignments posted on Canvas approximately weekly.
        There are more practice problems available in the course notes.
        Doing homework problems is the primary way that you will learn and internalize the material seen in class.
        Plan to spend a substantial amount of time throughout the semester doing homework problems.
      </p>
    </paragraphs>


    <paragraphs>
      <title>Quizzes</title>

      <p>
        There will be in-class quizzes every other week (on Jan 20, Feb 3, Mar 10, Mar 24, and Apr 21).
        Quizzes give you some practice in a test-like environment without the same grade pressure as a test.
        The quizzes should be a signal to you about whether you're keeping up with the pace of the course.
      </p>
    </paragraphs>


    <paragraphs>
      <title>Exams</title>

      <p>
        This course will have two midterm exams and a Final Exam.
        Exams are the main opportunity for you to demonstrate your understanding of course material.
      </p>

      <p>
        <dl>
        <li>
          <title>Test 1</title>

          <p>
            Tuesday, February 17 (in class)
          </p>
        </li>

        <li>
          <title>Test 2</title>

          <p>
            Tuesday, April 7 (in class)
          </p>
        </li>

        <li>
          <title>Final Exam</title>

          <p>
            Tuesday, May 5, 10:30 am - 12:30 pm
          </p>
        </li>
        </dl>
      </p>
    </paragraphs>


    <paragraphs>
      <title>Makeup Policy</title>

      <p>
        There are no quiz or exam makeups.
        The lowest quiz will be dropped and replaced with the recitation score.
      </p>
    </paragraphs>
  </subsection>


